Justin Tyopuusu, Jalingo The Taraba State Independent Electoral Commission on Monday announced Saturday, May 16, 2020, as date for the Conduct of Local Government election in the State. The Chairman of the commission, Dr Philip Duwe, said this in Jalingo. Duwe explained that the budget for the conduct of the poll was approved since 2019, but the elections could not be done. “Today, February 10, 2020, the commission wishes to announce the commencement of the process to the conduct of the local government election into the 16 councils and 168 council wards in the state. “The process will go on within the minimum of 90 days as required by the law and election will be conducted by May 16, 2020,” he said. Copyright PUNCH.
